%h1 Request: Create Comment
.request.box
  .url
    POST /ideas/
    .placeholder<> idea ID
    \/comments.xml
  .parameters
    Post parameters:
    %ul
      %li
        %b comment[text]
  .response
    Response:
    = link 'Comment', 'responses/comment.html'
    or
    = link 'Validation Errors', 'responses/validation-errors.html'
%p
  Creates a new comment attached the idea with the given ID.
  %b Requires authentication.
%p== If the creation is successful, clients #{may} retrieve the ID of the new comment from the response. The server #{may} massage or sanitize user input. Therefore, if clients display the newly created comment after the request succeeds, they #{should} either re-read the comment text from the response or re-fetch the comment in a subsequent request.